.TH "hid_allocate_device" 9 "hid_allocate_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hid_allocate_device \- allocate new hid device descriptor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct hid_device *" hid_allocate_device
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Allocate and initialize hid device, so that hid_destroy_device might be
used to free it.

New hid_device pointer is returned on success, otherwise ERR_PTR encoded
error value.
